to the fact that the head expressed

38:09.000 --> 38:12.000
his general opinion about his employees.

38:12.000 --> 38:15.000
We don't really understand what this opinion is based on.

38:16.000 --> 38:19.000
It is very difficult for us to achieve a situation

38:19.000 --> 38:22.000
when the head of the department

38:22.000 --> 38:25.000
really gives the assessments

38:25.000 --> 38:28.000
in accordance with what he thinks about his employees.

38:28.000 --> 38:31.000
They are all different, right?

38:31.000 --> 38:34.000
It is rare that they are all the same.

38:34.000 --> 38:37.000
Here I offer several technologies.

38:37.000 --> 38:40.000
They are quite common.

38:40.000 --> 38:43.000
Let's look at the slide called simple arranging.

38:44.000 --> 38:47.000
Here they are arranged in simple alphabetical order.

38:47.000 --> 38:50.000
And then I, as a head,

38:50.000 --> 38:53.000
receive the following instruction

38:53.000 --> 38:56.000
from the person who conducts the assessment.

38:56.000 --> 38:59.000
I am asked to identify the best among my 9 employees,

38:59.000 --> 39:02.000
in this case 3 people,

39:02.000 --> 39:05.000
the best ones I have.

39:05.000 --> 39:08.000
I choose Bender, Kareiko and Polukhaev

39:08.000 --> 39:11.000
for different reasons,

39:12.000 --> 39:15.000
but I think they are the best.

39:15.000 --> 39:18.000
Now when I have done this,

39:18.000 --> 39:21.000
I am asked to identify the best among the remaining 3.

39:21.000 --> 39:24.000
I choose Bender, Kareiko and Polukhaev.

39:24.000 --> 39:27.000
The second group is Berlag, Gritsatsuev and Pannikovsky.

39:27.000 --> 39:30.000
Very good.

39:30.000 --> 39:33.000
I identified the best among the remaining 3.

39:33.000 --> 39:36.000
I was asked to do this.

39:36.000 --> 39:39.000
The rest are the worst.

39:39.000 --> 39:42.000
Here we use simple arranging.

39:42.000 --> 39:45.000
Good, bad, average.

39:45.000 --> 39:48.000
But if I had done this,

39:48.000 --> 39:51.000
I would have identified A or B,

39:51.000 --> 39:54.000
without taking any responsibility.

39:54.000 --> 39:57.000
They are all the same.

39:57.000 --> 40:00.000
But the technology we have just seen

40:00.000 --> 40:03.000
is called the forced choice method.

40:03.000 --> 40:06.000
I, as an assessor,

40:07.000 --> 40:10.000
use the technology of assessment

40:10.000 --> 40:13.000
to choose the best, the average and the worst.

40:13.000 --> 40:16.000
What would happen if I was asked

40:16.000 --> 40:19.000
to make a list of people to be fired?

40:19.000 --> 40:22.000
Let's say we decided to reduce the number of employees,

40:22.000 --> 40:25.000
and we think that the number is too large.

40:25.000 --> 40:28.000
I have a department, 9 people,

40:28.000 --> 40:31.000
let's leave 6 people.

40:31.000 --> 40:34.000
How would I react?

40:35.000 --> 40:38.000
In this situation,

40:38.000 --> 40:41.000
I would show my incompetence.

40:41.000 --> 40:44.000
There are cases when the manager says

40:44.000 --> 40:47.000
that he has a small number of people,

40:47.000 --> 40:50.000
and he needs more people.

40:50.000 --> 40:53.000
In this situation,

40:53.000 --> 40:56.000
this approach is effective.

40:56.000 --> 40:59.000
But we did not go into details

40:59.000 --> 41:02.000
why he considers the best employees

41:02.000 --> 41:05.000
and why he divides them.

41:05.000 --> 41:08.000
He simply divided them.

41:08.000 --> 41:11.000
This method can be carried out even easier

41:11.000 --> 41:14.000
by simply asking the assessor

41:14.000 --> 41:17.000
to list all the names

41:17.000 --> 41:20.000
in the order of the increase in the quality of work,

41:20.000 --> 41:23.000
again, according to the criteria

41:23.000 --> 41:26.000
of a good and a bad employee,

41:26.000 --> 41:29.000
in the order of the increase from the best to the worst.

41:30.000 --> 41:33.000
This will make it psychologically more difficult,

41:33.000 --> 41:36.000
because it is clear that several employees

41:36.000 --> 41:39.000
will be equally good, equally bad.

41:39.000 --> 41:42.000
Therefore, the method we have just considered

41:42.000 --> 41:45.000
is more comfortable for the assessor

41:45.000 --> 41:48.000
and morally justified.

41:50.000 --> 41:53.000
Let's consider a more complicated case.

41:53.000 --> 41:56.000
The question is,

41:56.000 --> 41:59.000
if we want to assess not one quality,

41:59.000 --> 42:02.000
not one indicator,

42:02.000 --> 42:05.000
but several,

42:05.000 --> 42:08.000
as we did earlier

42:08.000 --> 42:11.000
with the 360-degree assessment.

42:15.000 --> 42:18.000
Here we use a scale,

42:18.000 --> 42:21.000
which can be extended from three,

42:21.000 --> 42:24.000
but this is not very good,

42:24.000 --> 42:27.000
because you will usually get a 2 for everyone,

42:27.000 --> 42:30.000
and in very rare cases a 1 or a 3.

42:30.000 --> 42:33.000
You can get 5 points,

42:33.000 --> 42:36.000
but there is a high probability

42:36.000 --> 42:39.000
to get 3 and 4 for everyone,

42:39.000 --> 42:42.000
so it is best to use the assessment scales

42:42.000 --> 42:45.000
with a range of 7 or 10 points.

42:49.000 --> 42:52.000
The so-called Likert scale is used,

42:53.000 --> 42:56.000
which is extended from 0 to minus

42:56.000 --> 42:59.000
or from 0 to plus.

42:59.000 --> 43:02.000
In the picture you can see such a scale,

43:02.000 --> 43:05.000
where the assessment goes from minus 3 to plus 3.

43:08.000 --> 43:11.000
Here such indicators are assessed

43:11.000 --> 43:14.000
as workability, productivity, responsibility,

43:14.000 --> 43:17.000
independence, prioritization,

43:17.000 --> 43:20.000
ability to express your thoughts.

43:21.000 --> 43:24.000
The problem is what we mean

43:24.000 --> 43:27.000
by workability, productivity,

43:27.000 --> 43:30.000
independence, prioritization.

43:30.000 --> 43:33.000
If we go back to the 360-degree assessment,

43:33.000 --> 43:36.000
we saw that the person,

43:36.000 --> 43:39.000
his manager and his colleagues

43:39.000 --> 43:42.000
assess him in different ways,

43:42.000 --> 43:45.000
because they look at him from different points of view.

43:45.000 --> 43:48.000
For the manager,

43:49.000 --> 43:52.000
he is one, for his colleagues he is another,

43:52.000 --> 43:55.000
and for his subordinates he can be the third.

43:55.000 --> 43:58.000
This is where the problem arises,

43:58.000 --> 44:01.000
how to agree with the assessor

44:01.000 --> 44:04.000
what is workability,

44:04.000 --> 44:07.000
what is productivity, what is responsibility,

44:07.000 --> 44:10.000
and so on.

44:10.000 --> 44:13.000
To solve this problem,

44:13.000 --> 44:16.000
a special technology called

44:17.000 --> 44:20.000
the standard assessment sheet is created.

44:20.000 --> 44:23.000
This is a standard assessment sheet,

44:23.000 --> 44:26.000
which is used to tell the assessor

44:26.000 --> 44:29.000
what the assessment should mean.

44:29.000 --> 44:32.000
It is not just minus one,

44:32.000 --> 44:35.000
plus one, plus three,

44:35.000 --> 44:38.000
or plus five,

44:38.000 --> 44:41.000
but a clear and unambiguous understanding

44:41.000 --> 44:44.000
of what this assessment means,

44:44.000 --> 44:47.000
what the characteristics, qualities,

44:47.000 --> 44:50.000
and competencies are,

44:50.000 --> 44:53.000
and what the bad assessment is,

44:53.000 --> 44:56.000
what the average assessment is,

44:56.000 --> 44:59.000
and what the good assessment is.

44:59.000 --> 45:02.000
Let's compare two ways

45:02.000 --> 45:05.000
to assess a person.

45:05.000 --> 45:08.000
The standard assessment sheet

45:08.000 --> 45:11.000
and the traditional, classic, free-form assessment sheet.

45:12.000 --> 45:15.000
The assessment sheet is taken off the assessor

45:15.000 --> 45:18.000
and the task is to come up with an assessment.

45:18.000 --> 45:21.000
No one taught him this.

45:21.000 --> 45:24.000
It's a complicated procedure.

45:24.000 --> 45:27.000
Try to write in a free form

45:27.000 --> 45:30.000
your assessment of two or three qualities

45:30.000 --> 45:33.000
of your good friend.

45:33.000 --> 45:36.000
I assure you that this is not easy.

45:36.000 --> 45:39.000
Therefore, it often happens

45:40.000 --> 45:43.000
that people just rewrite the form

45:43.000 --> 45:46.000
from other characteristics.

45:46.000 --> 45:49.000
It turns out that all the characteristics

45:49.000 --> 45:52.000
are very similar to each other.

45:52.000 --> 45:55.000
The second point.

45:55.000 --> 45:58.000
If we use the free-form method,

45:58.000 --> 46:01.000
the assessor always has the opportunity

46:01.000 --> 46:04.000
to miss something,

46:04.000 --> 46:07.000
to give a biased answer,

46:08.000 --> 46:11.000
to give a biased answer.

46:11.000 --> 46:14.000
If we use the standard assessment sheet,

46:14.000 --> 46:17.000
then the person is forced to choose

46:17.000 --> 46:20.000
one of the assessments.

46:20.000 --> 46:23.000
He has no way to give such an answer

46:23.000 --> 46:26.000
that we do not understand what he means.

46:26.000 --> 46:29.000
Further.

46:29.000 --> 46:32.000
The number of interpretations

46:32.000 --> 46:35.000
is practically not given to the free-form characteristics.

46:36.000 --> 46:39.000
It's extremely difficult to do.

46:39.000 --> 46:42.000
The assessment sheet is suitable

46:42.000 --> 46:45.000
for such an interpretation,

46:45.000 --> 46:48.000
because it allows us to create a profile

46:48.000 --> 46:51.000
of the assessment of the employee.

46:51.000 --> 46:54.000
For each of the formulations

46:54.000 --> 46:57.000
of the assessment of certain qualities,

46:57.000 --> 47:00.000
we can hang points.

47:00.000 --> 47:03.000
The last point.

47:04.000 --> 47:07.000
The assessment of many people

47:07.000 --> 47:10.000
is very important.

47:10.000 --> 47:13.000
We evaluate candidates for promotion,

47:13.000 --> 47:16.000
the need for training and development,

47:16.000 --> 47:19.000
the performance of the personnel audit.

47:19.000 --> 47:22.000
The assessment sheet,

47:22.000 --> 47:25.000
which is broadcast in several scales,

47:25.000 --> 47:28.000
allows us to compare employees

47:28.000 --> 47:31.000
and analyze the picture

47:32.000 --> 47:35.000
of the company as a whole.

47:35.000 --> 47:38.000
The free-form characteristics

47:38.000 --> 47:41.000
do not allow us to do this,

47:41.000 --> 47:44.000
because they do not allow

47:44.000 --> 47:47.000
the above-mentioned number of comparisons.

47:47.000 --> 47:50.000
Such assessment sheets

47:50.000 --> 47:53.000
are the most versatile,

47:53.000 --> 47:56.000
convenient and common method

47:56.000 --> 47:59.000
of evaluating quality indicators.

47:59.000 --> 48:02.000
You can find many options in the literature,

48:02.000 --> 48:05.000
but practice shows that

48:05.000 --> 48:08.000
the assessment of the personnel

48:08.000 --> 48:11.000
in each situation,

48:11.000 --> 48:14.000
for each company,

48:14.000 --> 48:17.000
and taking into account the goals

48:17.000 --> 48:20.000
that are set before the assessment,

48:20.000 --> 48:23.000
you will have to develop it yourself.

48:23.000 --> 48:26.000
What are the requirements

48:26.000 --> 48:29.000
for the assessment of the personnel?

48:29.000 --> 48:32.000
The first requirement

48:32.000 --> 48:35.000
is to evaluate the performance

48:35.000 --> 48:38.000
of the personnel in the following terms.

48:38.000 --> 48:41.000
This means that the person

48:41.000 --> 48:44.000
behaves in a certain way,

48:44.000 --> 48:47.000
but does not give an abstract,

48:47.000 --> 48:50.000
vague assessment.

48:50.000 --> 48:53.000
The second requirement

48:53.000 --> 48:56.000
is to evaluate the performance

48:56.000 --> 48:59.000
of the personnel in the following terms.

48:59.000 --> 49:02.000
This significantly reduces

49:02.000 --> 49:05.000
the degree of subjectivity,

49:05.000 --> 49:08.000
but at the same time

49:08.000 --> 49:11.000
allows for quantitative assessment.

49:11.000 --> 49:14.000
The third requirement

49:14.000 --> 49:17.000
is the relevance of the work

49:17.000 --> 49:20.000
and the goals of the assessment.

49:21.000 --> 49:24.000
I would say that

49:24.000 --> 49:27.000
when you invent a form,

49:27.000 --> 49:30.000
you should follow

49:30.000 --> 49:33.000
one simple rule.

49:33.000 --> 49:36.000
If you have a form,

49:36.000 --> 49:39.000
tell yourself

49:39.000 --> 49:42.000
how to use it

49:42.000 --> 49:45.000
when you will be evaluating the personnel.

49:45.000 --> 49:48.000
If you are not able

49:49.000 --> 49:52.000
to explain why you need it,

49:52.000 --> 49:55.000
you should not do it.

49:55.000 --> 49:58.000
This significantly complicates the assessment.

49:58.000 --> 50:01.000
The last requirement

50:01.000 --> 50:04.000
is the principle of reasonable sufficientness.

50:04.000 --> 50:07.000
How many forms should be in the assessment sheet?

50:07.000 --> 50:10.000
As many as you need

50:10.000 --> 50:13.000
to evaluate a person

50:13.000 --> 50:16.000
and a group of people

50:16.000 --> 50:19.000
and to make the necessary decisions.

50:19.000 --> 50:22.000
Usually, this is not required.

50:22.000 --> 50:25.000
Let's look at some examples

50:25.000 --> 50:28.000
of the formulations from the assessment sheet.

50:28.000 --> 50:31.000
For example,

50:31.000 --> 50:34.000
the ability to allocate priorities in work.

50:34.000 --> 50:37.000
The highest grade D

50:37.000 --> 50:40.000
is absolutely clear

50:40.000 --> 50:43.000
and completely independent

50:43.000 --> 50:46.000
and knows how to allocate priorities.

50:46.000 --> 50:49.000
The average grade

50:49.000 --> 50:52.000
is able to allocate priorities,

50:52.000 --> 50:55.000
although it needs to be controlled.

50:55.000 --> 50:58.000
Or let's take the attitude

50:58.000 --> 51:01.000
of the people around them.

51:01.000 --> 51:04.000
The highest grade D

51:04.000 --> 51:07.000
is perfectly in line with the group

51:07.000 --> 51:10.000
and is respected.

51:10.000 --> 51:13.000
The lowest grade

51:13.000 --> 51:16.000
is the conflictive personality

51:16.000 --> 51:19.000
and negatively affects the relationship.

51:19.000 --> 51:22.000
The average grade

51:22.000 --> 51:25.000
is slightly better

51:25.000 --> 51:28.000
and is not attentive to the people around them.

51:28.000 --> 51:31.000
The average grade

51:31.000 --> 51:34.000
is not a serious complaint.

51:34.000 --> 51:37.000
These formulations are quite clear.

51:37.000 --> 51:40.000
It is important to discuss

51:40.000 --> 51:43.000
how a person responds to a particular formulation.

51:43.000 --> 51:46.000
The decision-making process

51:46.000 --> 51:49.000
is much easier for the evaluator.

51:49.000 --> 51:52.000
What else can we say about the assessment sheets?

51:52.000 --> 51:55.000
If we involve the leaders

51:55.000 --> 51:58.000
in the assessment of their subordinates,

51:58.000 --> 52:01.000
and we have to do it almost always,

52:01.000 --> 52:04.000
with a rare exception,

52:05.000 --> 52:08.000
our task is to facilitate

52:08.000 --> 52:11.000
the work of these people.

52:11.000 --> 52:14.000
Let's prepare better,

52:14.000 --> 52:17.000
sharpen our methodology,

52:17.000 --> 52:20.000
make a preliminary approval,

52:20.000 --> 52:23.000
and then start working.

52:23.000 --> 52:26.000
Thus, we solve the problem

52:26.000 --> 52:29.000
of efficiency of assessment.

52:29.000 --> 52:32.000
We do not assign the main work

52:32.000 --> 52:35.000
to the leaders,

52:35.000 --> 52:38.000
but we do it for them.

52:38.000 --> 52:41.000
Thus, you will be able

52:41.000 --> 52:44.000
to facilitate the assessment of your staff

52:44.000 --> 52:47.000
and to win the respect

52:47.000 --> 52:50.000
of the leaders

52:50.000 --> 52:53.000
of the subordinates

52:53.000 --> 52:56.000
you will involve in this work.

53:02.000 --> 53:05.000
The most important part of the lesson

53:05.000 --> 53:08.000
So, dear colleagues,

53:08.000 --> 53:11.000
we are starting

53:11.000 --> 53:14.000
the most important and, I think,

53:14.000 --> 53:17.000
interesting part of our lesson.

53:17.000 --> 53:20.000
We have found out

53:20.000 --> 53:23.000
why the assessment of staff is necessary,

53:23.000 --> 53:26.000
we have found out

53:26.000 --> 53:29.000
what technologies and methods

53:29.000 --> 53:32.000
are used in the assessment of staff,

53:32.000 --> 53:35.000
and now we have to put it all together

53:35.000 --> 53:38.000
and agree on how you will

53:38.000 --> 53:41.000
implement the assessment of staff

53:41.000 --> 53:44.000
in your practice if you are given

53:44.000 --> 53:47.000
such a task.

53:47.000 --> 53:50.000
We will consider the following questions.

53:50.000 --> 53:53.000
First, the criteria of efficiency

53:53.000 --> 53:56.000
of assessment of staff,

53:56.000 --> 53:59.000
what you need to do

53:59.000 --> 54:02.000
and what dangers and obstacles

54:02.000 --> 54:05.000
you need to avoid in order to get

54:05.000 --> 54:08.000
good, pleasant and positive results.

54:08.000 --> 54:11.000
We will see what can prevent this,

54:11.000 --> 54:14.000
and finally we will go through

54:14.000 --> 54:17.000
the algorithm of planning and assessment

54:17.000 --> 54:20.000
of staff.

54:20.000 --> 54:23.000
You can highlight five criteria

54:24.000 --> 54:27.000
The first criteria is the purpose.

54:27.000 --> 54:30.000
You need to clearly formulate the purpose

54:30.000 --> 54:33.000
of the assessment and the criteria for its achievement.

54:33.000 --> 54:36.000
What does it mean?

54:36.000 --> 54:39.000
You need to formulate the purpose of the assessment

54:39.000 --> 54:42.000
of staff in such terms, so that when you

54:42.000 --> 54:45.000
carry it out, you can clearly say whether

54:45.000 --> 54:48.000
it was successful or not.

54:48.000 --> 54:51.000
And if it was not successful, then how many percent?

54:52.000 --> 54:55.000
The second criteria is the result.

54:55.000 --> 54:58.000
As we have already said, the assessment of staff

54:58.000 --> 55:01.000
is not the goal itself.

55:01.000 --> 55:04.000
It is always aimed at achieving

55:04.000 --> 55:07.000
specific results and at performing

55:07.000 --> 55:10.000
some management actions,

55:10.000 --> 55:13.000
decisions and actions in relation to

55:13.000 --> 55:16.000
the staff of our company.

55:16.000 --> 55:19.000
Who to train, who to raise,

55:20.000 --> 55:23.000
who to leave alone,

55:23.000 --> 55:26.000
and who, unfortunately, will have to leave

55:26.000 --> 55:29.000
our company.

55:29.000 --> 55:32.000
Be sure to make decisions based on the results of the assessment.

55:32.000 --> 55:35.000
The third criteria is the effectiveness of the assessment

55:35.000 --> 55:38.000
of costs.

55:38.000 --> 55:41.000
We have already been able to make sure that

55:41.000 --> 55:44.000
the assessment of staff is a difficult and difficult matter.

55:44.000 --> 55:47.000
Therefore, it is not necessary to give a situation

55:47.000 --> 55:50.000
where you have to make a decision

55:50.000 --> 55:53.000
based on the results of the assessment.

55:53.000 --> 55:56.000
The next important criterion is the positive

55:56.000 --> 55:59.000
impact of the assessment on organizational culture

55:59.000 --> 56:02.000
and the relationship of people in the organization.

56:02.000 --> 56:05.000
The assessment of staff should strengthen the organization,

56:05.000 --> 56:08.000
not harm it.

56:08.000 --> 56:11.000
Unfortunately, it often turns out that the assessment

56:11.000 --> 56:14.000
of staff leads to demoralization of employees,

56:15.000 --> 56:18.000
but it is not a problem.

56:18.000 --> 56:21.000
The next criterion is the continuity and development.

56:21.000 --> 56:24.000
It is not necessary to assess the staff once,

56:24.000 --> 56:27.000
and then forget that it exists.

56:27.000 --> 56:30.000
It will be effective if it is carried out regularly,

56:30.000 --> 56:33.000
constantly, at least once a year,

56:33.000 --> 56:36.000
if it is corrected in accordance with the gained experience,

56:36.000 --> 56:39.000
and if it is changed in accordance with the new goals

56:39.000 --> 56:42.000
and tasks of your organization.

56:42.000 --> 56:45.000
This allows you to spend 3-5 years

56:45.000 --> 56:48.000
analyzing the results of the assessment

56:48.000 --> 56:51.000
and see which way the staff policy of your company

56:51.000 --> 56:54.000
and its staff potential are moving.

56:54.000 --> 56:57.000
I must say that today this is one of the most important tasks

56:57.000 --> 57:00.000
of the management of the organization's staff.

57:03.000 --> 57:06.000
What can prevent us?

57:06.000 --> 57:09.000
The first thing that we often face

57:09.000 --> 57:12.000
is the lack of understanding of the company,

57:12.000 --> 57:15.000
the clear understanding of the goals and expected results.

57:15.000 --> 57:18.000
Let's assess the staff. Why?

57:18.000 --> 57:21.000
Well, others do it, and we will assess it.

57:21.000 --> 57:24.000
We also often have to face such a wonderful phrase

57:24.000 --> 57:27.000
that something is stuck in our company,

57:27.000 --> 57:30.000
we need to make something up.

57:30.000 --> 57:33.000
Unfortunately, it turns out that the torment

57:33.000 --> 57:36.000
of the situation in the company

57:36.000 --> 57:39.000
